"'''Jim Puntasen''' has joined the P2P Foundation since November 2005, and he is the weekly blogger on Thai P2P developments, as in sanook.com and blogger.com. He translated the basic essay on the Political Economy of Peer Production in the Thai language.

Jim also currently works as a researcher for RASMI, which is the institute  devoting  for the  economic  and  social  reforms  in Thailand,  where   equal   opportunities  and sustainable coorporation are respected- and he had previously served as a journalist
for Thailand's indepedent newspaper, The Nation. 

His mail address is jim.puntasen@gmail.com "

